OL,3,CUK must prepare for 2C of global
OL,4,Cwarming by 2050, climate advisors warn
OL,6,FThe review, commissioned by Flooding
OL,7,FMinister Emma Hardy, concluded in
OL,8,FApril at the Climate Change Committee:
OL,9,F"There is now unequivocal evidence
OL,10,Fthat climate change is making extreme
OL,11,Fweather in the UK more likely and more
OL,12,Fextreme.
OL,14,F"Across the UK, this looks like
OL,15,Fheatwaves, heavy rainfall, and
OL,16,Fwildfire-conducive conditions. The UK
OL,17,Fis not appropriately prepared for
OL,18,Fthis. Notably, there has been no
OL,19,Fchange in addressing this risk with
OL,20,Fthe change in government."
